.8pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What will the local environmental impact (for example air po</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">llution) be from the use heat generation in urban areas, for example CHP units?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Negligible.  A static 1 MW engine burning natural gas, properly set up, will have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">very low emissions compared to what is generated by road vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> consuming fossil fuel at a c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">omparable rate.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">  A fuel cell CHP unit would emit only </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; font-style:italic; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">– </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">no particulates</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">NOx</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">; additionally, it would be very quiet.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.8pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent