 the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Everything in this country is driven by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">American-style </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">short-term </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">individualist </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">thinking, and there is scant regard for The Public Good.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">  Contrast with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Scandinavia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.8pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What are the lock-in, costs and GHG savings from the promotion of different form</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s of domestic heating solution?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">This question is so poorly worded, it makes no sense.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.8pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Should the government take any further any specific actions in relation to cooling?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">This </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">question is so poorly worded, it makes no sense.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Why does the RHI not seem to promote heat pumps successfully?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">The story of RHI has been such a stop/start farce, most people assume it either no longer exists, or they assume that, as with PV FITs, promises </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">will be reneged on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">: once bitten, thrice shy.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">How successful will the RHI be when rolled out to households?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">This question is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">arrogantly presumptuous: RHI will be a flop, because nobody </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">will trust any </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">promises made </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">relating to RHI.  The recent history</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> of grants and schemes etc. can be summarised by a cycle of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">promise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">s – commercial enthusiasm – public adoption – </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">government panic – government back-tracking </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">and betrayal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">– commercial ruin – public mistrust of the technology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Thermal storage is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> potential useful method of balancing electricity/energy demand both diurnally and annually.  What is government policy doing to promote thermal storage, and should it do more/different?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Thermal storage is key to generation and grid stability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">: it is much e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">asier to store heat compared to electricity.  However, as with all the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">electricity supply </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">problems facing us, thermal storage coupled with heat pumps will NOT work </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">unless the electricity grid is being operated for the Public Good</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">, and not as a speculative </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">trading floor.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">  Furthermore, the bid-offer price disparity for privately generated green electricity M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">UST be narrowed: at the moment m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ore and more people are getting FIT payments, but converting the green electricity they produce to heat (using such device</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">s as EMMA and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Immersun</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">) because </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">they are offered far too little </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">money </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">for the power they produce: they are being paid to feed in, but they are damned if they will feed in!</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">FIT </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">should be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">replaced by a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">net </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">reen </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">generation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">credit </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">only payable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">for electric</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ity exported onto the grid, reversing the disincentive scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> operating at the moment.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>